    <section id="how-to-read">
      <h2>How to read this page</h2>
      <p class="lead">We separate <span class="chip fact">facts</span> from <span class="chip assumption">assumptions</span> and <span class="chip inference">inferences</span>. Every forward‑looking statement includes a time horizon, a metric, a probability, and what would falsify it. Credibility is scored with a transparent rubric.</p>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Credibility rubric (per claim)</strong>: R1 Evidence quality (25%), R2 Track record (20%), R3 Causal coherence (20%), R4 Corroboration (15%), R5 Specificity/Falsifiability (15%), R6 Conflict/Incentives (5%, reverse‑scored). Weighted total: 0–100.</li>
        <li><strong>Horizon &amp; metric</strong> tell you <em>what precisely</em> we will check and by <em>what date</em>.</li>
        <li><strong>Falsifiers</strong> are concrete thresholds that, if crossed, flip the scenario probabilities.</li>
      </ul>
    </section>

