        <div>
          <h3><span class="pill base">Base</span> Soft‑ish landing &amp; shallow deceleration <span class="prob">(p = 0.55)</span></h3>
          <ul>
            <li><strong>Growth:</strong> 2026 real GDP (Q4/Q4) <strong>1.5–2.0%</strong> <a class="ref" href="#ref-8">[R8]</a>.</li>
            <li><strong>Inflation:</strong> Core PCE in Dec‑26 <strong>2.5–2.8%</strong> <a class="ref" href="#ref-3">[R3]</a>.</li>
            <li><strong>Policy:</strong> Fed funds by Dec‑26 <strong>3.25–3.50%</strong> <a class="ref" href="#ref-2">[R2]</a>.</li>
            <li><strong>Rates:</strong> 10Y UST <strong>3.6–4.4%</strong>; modest steepening.</li>
            <li><strong>Credit:</strong> HY OAS averages <strong>300–400 bps</strong> with temporary spikes <a class="ref" href="#ref-7">[R7]</a>.</li>
            <li><strong>Equities:</strong> 12M TR <strong>+6% to +12%</strong>; pullbacks of <strong>10–15%</strong> likely.</li>
            <li><strong>Gold:</strong> Mostly in <strong>$3.6–4.4k</strong>; upside skew persists <a class="ref" href="#ref-18">[R18]</a>.</li>
            <li><strong>Oil:</strong> 2026 Brent average <strong>$50–60</strong> <a class="ref" href="#ref-11">[R11]</a>.</li>
          </ul>
          <p class="legend"><em>Falsify:</em> two core PCE prints &lt; 2.4% (faster disinflation) or ≥ 3.1% for three prints; 10Y TIPS ≥ 2.1% without crisis.</p>
        </div>

        <div>
          <h3><span class="pill bull">Bull</span> Productivity upside <span class="prob">(p = 0.20)</span></h3>
          <ul>
            <li><strong>Growth:</strong> AI‑linked capex raises TFP; breadth widens.</li>
            <li><strong>Inflation:</strong> Core PCE <strong>2.3–2.5%</strong> in 2026.</li>
            <li><strong>Policy:</strong> FFR gravitates to ~<strong>3.0%</strong>.</li>
            <li><strong>Equities:</strong> 12–24M TR <strong>+15–25%</strong>; small‑cap quality leads.</li>
            <li><strong>Gold:</strong> Drifts toward <strong>$3.5–4.2k</strong>.</li>
          </ul>
          <p class="legend"><em>Falsify:</em> stalled productivity data; sticky services inflation; weak capex.</p>
        </div>

        <div>
          <h3><span class="pill bear">Bear</span> Policy accident / sticky services <span class="prob">(p = 0.25)</span></h3>
