    <section id="falsifiers">
      <h2>Falsifiers &amp; tripwires (what would change the call)</h2>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Inflation undershoots:</strong> core PCE &lt; <strong>2.4% YoY</strong> for two consecutive prints → upgrade “Productivity upside” scenario; increase duration and small‑cap quality exposure <a class="ref" href="#ref-3">[R3]</a>.</li>
        <li><strong>Sticky inflation with high real rates:</strong> core PCE ≥ <strong>3.1%</strong> for three prints <em>and</em> 10Y TIPS ≥ <strong>2.1%</strong> → raise “Policy accident” scenario; cut equity beta; wait to add rates <a class="ref" href="#ref-5">[R5]</a>.</li>
        <li><strong>Credit wobble:</strong> HY OAS &gt; <strong>400 bps</strong> without recession data → start adding BB/B; **&gt; 550 bps** = strong buy basket, ex‑CCC <a class="ref" href="#ref-7">[R7]</a>.</li>
        <li><strong>Oil divergence:</strong> Brent &gt; <strong>$75</strong> for 3 consecutive months → higher breakevens; rotate some grid/utilities to energy beta; add breakeven exposure <a class="ref" href="#ref-11">[R11]</a>.</li>
        <li><strong>Tariff pass‑through:</strong> core goods inflation &gt; <strong>+1.5% YoY</strong> sustained → haircut margin expectations in low‑ticket importers; avoid chasing EPS ramps <a class="ref" href="#ref-14">[R14]</a>.</li>
      </ul>
