      <p>Our modal path is a <strong>soft‑ish landing with a shallow deceleration</strong> (p≈0.55): growth cools but stays positive, core PCE drifts toward the high‑2s, and the Fed cuts gradually to the mid‑3s by end‑2026. Valuation, not earnings, is the near‑term risk: a thin equity risk premium and positive real rates mean <strong>drawdowns of 10–15%</strong> can happen without a recession. Credit is priced close to perfection; wait for <strong>HY OAS &gt; 400 bps</strong> to add. Gold likely <strong>range‑trades $3.5–4.5k</strong> with an upside skew if policy/geopolitical risk flares. Oil’s base case drifts lower into 2026, helping disinflation along. Watch our falsifiers—especially core PCE, real TIPS yields, credit spreads, and Brent—because they will move the probabilities faster than narratives will.</p>
